AC  GenProp0798
DE  Enterococcus/Aeromonas extended locus
TP  SYSTEM
AU  Haft DH
TH  0
CC  This Genome Property represents an uncharacterized, sporadically
CC  distributed eight-gene system. A somewhat broader set of bacteria
CC  contain three core genes from this system including a probable
CC  amidohydrolase (TIGR03583), a pyridoxal phosphate-dependent enzyme
CC  related to SelA (TIGR01437), and an uncharacterized protein
CC  (TIGR03581). Species with the eight-gene system include Aeromonas
CC  hydrophila ATCC7966, Salmonella typhimurium LT2, and Vibrio fischeri
CC  ES114 among the Proteobacteria, and Enterococcus faecalis V583 and
CC  Bacillus clausii KSM-K16 among the Firmicutes. The three-gene core is
CC  found also in Lactobacillus plantarum WCFS1, Bacillus anthracis, and
CC  Clostridium difficile QCD-32g58. Neighboring genes, including
CC  PTS-family transport genes and a member of the carbohydrate kinases,
CC  tend to suggest a role in carbohydrate catabolism.
--
